Class Property

java.lang.Object
Objects.Property
public class Property extends Object
Represents a property with a name, type, available dates, and reservations. Each date has its own base pricing, environmental rate, and reservation status.

  • Constructor Details

    • Property

      public Property(String name)
      Constructs a Property with the given name. The default property type is Eco-Apartment. The property can store up to 30 dates and 30 reservations.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the property

    • Property

      public Property(String name, PropertyType type)
      Constructs a Property with a specific name and type. Initializes storage for up to 30 dates and 30 reservations.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the property
      type - the property type

      Parameters:
      date - the Date to add

    • removeDate

      Parameters:

    • addReservation

      public boolean addReservation(Reservation res)
      Adds a reservation if all requested dates exist and are available. When added, all corresponding Date objects are marked as reserved.
      Parameters:
      res - the reservation to add
      Returns:
      true if added successfully; false otherwise

    • removeReservation

      public boolean removeReservation(Reservation res)
      Removes a reservation and resets the reservation status of its dates.
      Parameters:
      res - the reservation to remove
      Returns:
      true if removed; false otherwise
